uenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."],"variants":[{"name":"Tricot","meanings":["(2010: NA)","French:","nickname from a diminutive of <i>trique</i> ‘cudgel’."]},{"name":"Trago","meanings":["Variant of   Trego  , a surname of Cornish and French origin. In the US, it is found mainly in PA and OH."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry de Tregoz was born before 1181, in Sussex, England, United Kingdom, his father, John de Tregoz, was 11177 and his mother, Amice fitz Gerold, was 11177. He had at least 1 son with Mrs De Tregoz. He died before 1256, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Bef 1181–Bef 1256":"enne 1181–enne 1256","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1181–1256":"1181–1256","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1203–1270":"1203–1270","1137–1195":"1137–1195","1141–1188":"1141–1188","1141":"1141","1195":"1195","1270":"1270","1181":"1181","1180":"1180","1137":"1137","1203":"1203","Bef 1256":"enne 1256","1256":"1256","Bef 8 April 1195":"enne 8. aprilli 1195","1188":"1188","about 1203":"umbes 1203","before 1181":"enne 1181","Bef 1181":"enne 1181","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sussex, England":"Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","East Preston, Sussex, England":"East Preston, Sussex, England"},"fi":{"Bef 1181–Bef 1256":"ennen vuotta 1181–ennen vuotta 1256","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut"